President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday told lawmakers to behave themselves when they made several attempts to jeer him during budget presentation. The president told the jeering lawmakers, most of whom are members of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, that “May I remind the Hon members that the world is watching. We are supposed to be above this.” Our correspondent reports that many PDP Reps kept jeering the president intermittently during the budget presentation, while their APC counterparts kept on cheering him. DSS, police takeover N/Assembly as Buhari presents budget today Breaking: PDP Reps set to protest as Buhari presents budget Budget Presentation: Pandemonium as placard carrying PDP Reps chant "Freedom comes by struggle"